Program: Discovery
Title: Cancer and cachexia
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwm7
Last Broadcast Date: 26 February 1996
Scientists believe they have found the cause of wasting in cancer and Aids patients. Scientists find cause of cachexia during cancer, which causes the body to waste away. Also in the programme the COAST telescope which has been built in Cambridge, and the protein pipes discovered in both brains and carrots. Presenter: Roland Pease. Show less